If I didn’t have videos of me smiling I’d be convinced that the only thing I felt this year was sadness. That’s how easy it is to get stuck in my head. For anyone who might be struggling here’s my advice: When you feel helpless, just hold out one more day. I don’t care what the reason is… do everything you can to go one more day. What you’ll find out later is that somehow you came up with 365 reasons to stay alive. I’m very grateful to have made it through 2022 and thank you to everyone who has lifted me up ♥️ #HappyNewYear #mentalhealthawareness

Episode 2 of Wellness Wednesday… It was a pretty exhausting week but by day 5 I was feeling great and I think it’s probably the cold water from the swim that helped a lot. I also did not realize how exhausting swinging a bat was (obviously it’s been a while 😩). I’m going to incorporate fun things like that during my training so I don’t get bored of just being in the gym. The hardest part about all of this is balancing my work schedule with my training schedule. I have given myself 5 non negotiable workout days a week. Which is really helpful because my 2 rest days don’t always fall next to each other when work gets crazy. I really like making these videos and I hope you enjoy my recaps 🏋🏾 fyi, sometimes I’ll play my unreleased songs in the background 👀🫢 #melayamusic #wellnesswednesday #fitnessjourney #running

This was a big “no one can change YOUR life but you” moment. It’s hard to admit that being miserable and unhappy can come from within. It’s easy to blame others and blame your situation and say “They just don’t understand. I’m doing my best”. Lying to yourself is a whole lot easier than putting in the work to change your life. This song came from the moment I said to myself “take the risk, try to be better, and no matter what I got you”. The moment I knew I had my own back was the moment I could see life a bit clearer. And I could only have my own back if I lead with honesty and vulnerability. #memorablelyrics #melayamusic #quotes

I’m pro internet creators FOREVER! Make your videos, be “cringey”, do what you want. The early YouTubers not only paved the way for the new age influencers but for the new age post production crew as well. When I first got to LA in 2014 I chose to go the internet route and it’s the best decision I ever made. I had time to learn and make mistakes before things got over saturated. It honestly felt like I got snuck into the industry and then one day I was finally as good as everyone else. Today, that back door isn’t as easy to find and the internet has so much competition. But if you’re an aspiring creator the best thing you can do is KEEP CREATING. And when you get the chance, ride that wave 🌊🎬 #influencer #filmmaker #melayamusic

October was fun. Here’s some highlights! I kinda wrote a lot of songs. Like way more than any other month… so that’s amazing ☺️ Other than that, I’ve been running and editing a lot. My mental health has been in a great place. I don’t remember the last time I’ve been this consistently happy with life. The biggest change is in how I deal with problem solving and anxiety. Anyways, I’m looking forward to the rest of the year even though my schedule might get a little hectic from time to time. Only having 2 months left of 2023 is a wild feeling. And let me just say, I feel very privileged to exist in this world. It needs a lot of fixing but I like to think that if you love your home then you should fight for it.
